The paper proposes a framework for modelling sparse, high-dimensional, and overdispersed discrete data using variational autoencoders. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as well as Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also applies the proposed framework to text analysis, collaborative filtering, and multi-label learning, indicating that it may belong to the sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
